        "introduction-to-iot-agents" : {"priority":6,"track":"Tech Training","moderated":false,"session":"FIWARE Training","prefix":"Training","title":"Introduction to IoT Agents","date":"2001-05-21T22:00:00.000Z","start":"3:00 pm","end":"3:30 pm","location":"Room Jbel Ayachi","img":"https://www.fiware.org/fiware-summit/assets/icons/icon-dev-training.svg","description":"<p>Connecting IoT devices or “things” involves the need to overcome a common set of problems arising in the different layers of the communication model. Using sensor data or acting upon them requires interaction with a heterogeneous environment of devices running different protocols (due to the lack of globally accepted standards), dispersed and accessible through multiple wireless technologies.</p>","excerpt":"Connecting IoT devices or “things” involves the need to overcome a common set of problems arising in the different layers of the communication model.","publish":true,"moderators":[],"speakers":[{"title":"","name":"Jason Fox","surname":"Fox","image":"jason-fox.jpg","company":"FIWARE Foundation","companyType":"","website":"https://www.fiware.org/","job":"Senior Technical Expert & Evangelist","bio":"Jason Fox (m) has been working for FIWARE Foundation for the last six years in the role of technical evangelist, educating and diseminating information about NGSI interfaces, JSON-LD, Linked Data, the components within the FIWARE Catalogue and Securing FIWARE architectures. Before joining FIWARE, he worked as a software engineer for over 20 years in various roles both in Germany and the United Kingdom using a wide variety of programming languages ranging from C++ to Java to Node.js. This has included coding the software behind selling lottery tickets online for the British National Lottery, and and developing and maintaining technical documentation applications for Nokia.","linkedIn":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/jason-fox-8a79563/","twitter":"","filters":["Expert","Evangelist"],"email":"","publish":true,"img":"https://www.fiware.org/wp-content/directories/people/images/200px/jason-fox.jpg","flagUrl":"https://www.fiware.org/wp-content/directories/people/images/flag","shortJob":"Expert"}],"startTime":"2001-05-22T13:00:00.000Z","shortDate":"22 May","social":"/fgs-2025/introduction-to-iot-agents.html","socialImage":"/fgs-2025/introduction-to-iot-agents.png","trackColor":"light-green","numSpeakers":1},
        "data-as-a-strategic-asset--lessons-from-porto-s-urban-platform-and-the-beopen-project" : {"priority":2,"track":"AI & Data-Driven Urban Mngmt","moderated":false,"session":"When Intelligence Meets Endurance: AI & Data-Driven Cities for the FIFA World Cup 2030","prefix":"","title":"Data as a Strategic Asset: Lessons from Porto’s Urban Platform and the BeOpen Project","date":"2001-05-21T22:00:00.000Z","start":"3:20 pm","end":"3:30 pm","location":"Auditorium","img":"https://www.fiware.org/fiware-summit/assets/icons/icon-urban-mngmt.svg","description":"","excerpt":"","publish":true,"moderators":[],"speakers":[{"name":"Joäo Bastos"}],"startTime":"2001-05-22T13:20:00.000Z","shortDate":"22 May","social":"/fgs-2025/data-as-a-strategic-asset--lessons-from-porto-s-urban-platform-and-the-beopen-project.html","socialImage":"/fgs-2025/data-as-a-strategic-asset--lessons-from-porto-s-urban-platform-and-the-beopen-project.png","trackColor":"light-purple","numSpeakers":1},
        "european-local-digital-twin-toolbox-project---advancing-the-digital-maturity-of-cities" : {"priority":4,"track":"Tech & Trends","moderated":false,"session":"Digital Twins for Real-Time Optimization of Sporting Mega-Events","prefix":"","title":"European Local Digital Twin Toolbox Project - Advancing the Digital Maturity of Cities","date":"2001-05-21T22:00:00.000Z","start":"4:00 pm","end":"4:10 pm","location":"","img":"https://www.fiware.org/fiware-summit/assets/icons/icon-trends-training.svg","description":"","excerpt":"","publish":true,"moderators":[],"speakers":[{"title":"","name":"Antonio Jara","surname":"Jara","image":"antonio-jara.jpg","company":"Libelium","companyType":"","website":"https://www.libelium.com/","job":"General Manager Smart Cities","bio":"Antonio has a PhD from the University of Murcia (Spain) and a MBA from the ENAE business school and UCAM (2012). He has received entrepreneurship awards from ENAE, emprendeGo, IPSO Alliance Award for its disruptive innovation in the IoT. As part of HOP Ubiquitous, Jara is focused on the Smart Cities market with solutions for citizens engagements, tourism, active participation, physical web and environmental monitoring (air quality sensors) in projects such as ENIAC SAFESENS, interoperability / pilots (SmartSDK, Synchronicity, Organicity, BeinCPPS) and also in several actions related to security/privacy (INPUT and FORTIKA).","linkedIn":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/jara-libelium/","twitter":"https://twitter.com/antonio_jara","filters":["General Manager"],"email":"","publish":true,"img":"https://www.fiware.org/wp-content/directories/people/images/200px/antonio-jara.jpg","flagUrl":"https://www.fiware.org/wp-content/directories/people/images/flag","shortJob":"General Manager"}],"startTime":"2001-05-22T14:00:00.000Z","shortDate":"22 May","social":"/fgs-2025/european-local-digital-twin-toolbox-project---advancing-the-digital-maturity-of-cities.html","socialImage":"/fgs-2025/european-local-digital-twin-toolbox-project---advancing-the-digital-maturity-of-cities.png","trackColor":"light-green","numSpeakers":1},
        "sdg-driven-solutions-for-a-sustainable-world-cup-legacy" : {"priority":5,"track":"Sustainable Smart City","moderated":false,"session":"","prefix":"","title":"SDG-Driven Solutions for a Sustainable World Cup Legacy","date":"2001-05-21T22:00:00.000Z","start":"4:00 pm","end":"5:00 pm","location":"Auditorium","img":"https://www.fiware.org/fiware-summit/assets/icons/icon-sustainable-city.svg","description":"<p>This session highlights how sustainable energy and water management are essential to building climate-resilient cities ready to host the FIFA World Cup 2030. By integrating green technologies, digital water solutions, and circular economy models, Morocco can ensure resource efficiency and environmental stewardship. These innovations not only support the demands of a global event but also lay the groundwork for a lasting, sustainable urban legacy.</p>","excerpt":"This session highlights how sustainable energy and water management are essential to building climate-resilient cities ready to host the FIFA World Cup 2030.","publish":true,"moderators":[],"speakers":[],"startTime":"2001-05-22T14:00:00.000Z","shortDate":"22 May","social":"/fgs-2025/sdg-driven-solutions-for-a-sustainable-world-cup-legacy.html","socialImage":"/fgs-2025/sdg-driven-solutions-for-a-sustainable-world-cup-legacy.png","trackColor":"light-blue","numSpeakers":0},
